  "text": "The Chromium Blink rendering pipeline stages are implemented in the following key C++ source files:\n\n1. **StyleResolver** (third_party/blink/renderer/core/css/resolver/style_resolver.h): The class that resolves computed styles for DOM elements. It is declared as `class CORE_EXPORT StyleResolver final : public GarbageCollected<StyleResolver>` at line 63. This class is responsible for selecting a ComputedStyle for a given element in a document based on the document's collection of stylesheets.\n\n2. **LayoutObject** (third_party/blink/renderer/core/layout/layout_object.h): The base class for the layout tree. It is declared as `class CORE_EXPORT LayoutObject : public GarbageCollected<LayoutObject>, public ImageResourceObserver, public DisplayItemClient` at line 270. This is a fundamental class that represents an object in the layout tree.\n\n3. **PaintLayer** (third_party/blink/renderer/core/paint/paint_layer.h): The painting layer abstraction that handles complex painting operations. It is declared as `class CORE_EXPORT PaintLayer : public GarbageCollected<PaintLayer>, public DisplayItemClient` at line 174. PaintLayer is central to painting and hit-testing.\n\n4. **PaintController** (third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/paint/paint_controller.h): The controller responsible for processing display items as they are produced and producing a final paint artifact. It is declared as `class PLATFORM_EXPORT PaintController` at line 131. The class includes logic for caching, cache invalidation, and merging.\n\n5. **DisplayItemList** (third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/paint/display_item_list.h): The display list that records paint operations as a container for a list of display items of various types. It is declared as `class PLATFORM_EXPORT DisplayItemList` at line 28.\n\nThese classes form the core of the rendering pipeline: StyleResolver resolves CSS styles → LayoutObject creates the layout tree → PaintLayer organizes layers for painting → PaintController manages display items and paint operations → DisplayItemList stores the final paint commands for rendering."
}

